description:
&lt;p&gt;With COVID-19 continuing to play a major part in all our everyday lives, we are expanding our capacity over the winter period and need your support to help deliver excellent care to our patients. We can offer ad-hoc shifts and/or longer-term placements through our Staff Bank, to work around your commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a qualified Health Visitor or currently studying the Specialist Community Public Health Nurse training in Health Visiting?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a retired nurse looking to return to practice?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a difference and be part of further developing our service?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’ve answered ‘yes’, we’d love to talk to you about joining one of our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CLCH NHS Trust is currently re-shaping the way Health Visitors work, looking at new and innovative practices to improve health across London. This includes agile working and provision of laptops to all staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a range of Health Visiting posts across the trust, offering good professional development opportunities, working with diverse populations. We are developing innovative models of working with our families and partner agencies to offer high quality care to achieve positive outcomes for families in London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are excited by the above then we would love to hear from you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our temporary staffing shifts are calculated hourly and paid weekly. You are paid only for the hours you actually work during any Assignment. Bank workers are paid on fixed third point based on the Agenda for Change (AFC) pay bands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HCAS: Inner 20% - Outer 15% - Fringe 5% (As per AfC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Weekly pay will include: Basic pay + HCAS + 12.07% Holiday pay + Unsocial hours (If applicable)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
